{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 User Manual \u8212- Lucie: Salesforce Doc Generator\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\i Version: April 2026 \u8212- Language: English}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Lucie is a Python application ({\f1 Tkinter} UI) that extracts metadata from a Salesforce org through the {\f1 sf} CLI and produces:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab a navigable HTML documentation (objects, fields, validation rules, flows, Apex, OmniStudio, Profiles / Permission Sets, executive index);\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Excel workbooks (permission sets, profiles, metadata inventory, PMD);\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab a {\b complexity score} and an {\b Adopt vs Adapt} score with fully configurable weights;\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab a configurable {\b static analyzer} (PMD rules + Well-Architected + Admin best practices);\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab an {\b AI assistant} (Claude / Gemini) to chat about the documented org.\sa180\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
