{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\f1 Tkinter} ships with Python on Windows.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Step-by-step install\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 From the application folder ({\f1 c:\\...\\HtmlDocGenerator\\2026}):\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 python -m venv .venv\line
.venv\\Scripts\\activate\line
pip install -r requirements.txt\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\f1 requirements.txt} installs (among others) {\f1 openpyxl} (Excel), {\f1 anthropic} (Claude) and {\f1 google-generativeai} (Gemini).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Local preferences\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The application keeps its preferences in {\f1 app_settings.json} at the project root (language, alias, folders, API keys, scoring weights, system prompt, analyzer rules etc.). This file stays local (it is listed in {\f1 .gitignore}).\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 2. Launching the application\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 python app.py\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 On first launch the default language is {\b French}. Use the language combo at the top right of the main window to switch \u8212- every label, log message and heading is translated live.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The main window exposes two tabs:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Documentation}: full retrieve + generation pipeline.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Discussion}: chat with an AI assistant using the documented org as context.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The menu bar also provides:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Downloads}: shortcuts to external tools (SF CLI, PMD, Org Check).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Configuration}: settings window, complexity score editor, Adopt vs Adapt editor.\sa180\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 3. Main window: Documentation tab\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The tab is split into three stacked blocks, followed by an execution log.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 3.1 Salesforce login\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab {\b Alias}: short name you pick for the org (stored by {\f1 sf}).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab {\b Environment}: {\f1 Production}, {\f1 Sandbox} or {\f1 Custom}. The {\b Instance URL} field is auto-filled ({\f1 https://login.salesforce.com} or {\f1 https://test.salesforce.com}) and becomes editable in Custom mode for My Domain / Enhanced Domain URLs.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab {\b Web login} button: opens your default browser on the Salesforce login page. After authentication, the CLI stores the access tokens.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 3.2 Org selection and CLI pipeline\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Below the login block:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Available orgs}: dropdown populated from {\f1 sf org list} (auto-refreshed at startup and via the {\b Refresh} button).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Generate manifest}: produces {\f1 package.xml} for the selected org (internally uses {\f1 sf project generate manifest}).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Retrieve}: runs {\f1 sf project retrieve start -x package.xml} against the selected org and writes the source tree to the retrieve folder.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Full pipeline}: chains manifest + retrieve + documentation generation in a single click.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Connection tokens and intermediary files land in {\f1 .sf_cli_project/} and {\f1 .sfdx/} (both ignored by git).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 3.3 ORG CHECK reports (optional)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b ORG CHECK report type}: {\f1 apex-classes}, {\f1 global-view} or {\f1 hardcoded-urls}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Generate ORG CHECK report}: runs the matching command and produces a summary Excel under {\f1 excel/}.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 3.4 Generation parameters\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Source folder}: root of a Salesforce retrieve (must contain {\f1 force-app/main/default/...}).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Output folder}: where the index, HTML, Excel and assets are written.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Exclusion file} {\i (optional)}: Excel workbook ({\f1 exclusion.xlsx}) listing artifacts to ignore (per type + name).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b PMD}: checkbox + ruleset {\f1 .xml} file. When enabled, PMD is run over the Apex source and violations are embedded in the HTML pages and exported to {\f1 pmd_violations.xlsx}.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 3.5 Running the generation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Generate documentation}: runs the pipeline against the source folder (no retrieve first). The button is disabled while a run is in progress.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Open index}: opens {\f1 index.html} in the default browser.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Execution log}: text area at the bottom; every step logs its progress (object count, classes, flows, analyzer findings etc.).\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 3.6 Reports to generate (checkbox inside Configuration)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The Configuration window lets you enable / disable:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab the documentation Excel workbooks;\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab the ORG CHECK reports.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Those toggles are persisted in {\f1 app_settings.json}.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 4. Main window: Discussion tab (AI)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The Discussion tab lets you chat with an AI assistant (Claude or Gemini) using the documented org as context.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Provider}: reflects the provider chosen in Configuration (Gemini by default).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Context status}:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab {\i "No context available"}: as long as no generation has been run, no org summary is sent to the model.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab {\i "Context available"}: after a run, a summary of the metadata (objects, Apex classes, flows, OmniStudio, analyzer findings, ...) is appended automatically under the system prompt for every message.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b History}: current conversation (blue = you, green = AI, grey = system, red = error).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Compose}: type your question and press {\f1 Enter} or click {\b Send}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Clear}: wipes the local history (does nothing on the provider side).\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The default system prompt explicitly tells the AI to walk source and documentation folders recursively before answering. You can tweak it in {\f1 Configuration > Discussion}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li720 \fi0 {\b Prerequisite}: the matching provider API key must be set under {\f1 Configuration > Discussion}. See {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "#11-how-to-get-a-gemini-api-key-and-a-claude-api-key"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
chapter 11
}}}
.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 5. Generated reports\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Inside the chosen output folder:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 <output>/\line
  index.html                    # Dashboard + Analyzer tab\line
  objects/<Object>.html         # Object page + Validation Rules tab + Analyzer\line
  apex/<Class>.html             # Apex page + heuristics + PMD + Analyzer\line
  flows/<Flow>.html             # Flow page + diagram + Analyzer\line
  omni/<Component>.html         # OmniStudio page (incl. Data Transforms)\line
  assets/                       # CSS, images, Mermaid / vis-network bundles\line
  excel/\line
    permission_sets.xlsx\line
    profiles.xlsx\line
    metadata_inventory.xlsx\line
    pmd_violations.xlsx         # only if PMD is enabled\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Interactive HTML pages\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Relationship / dependency graphs}: pan & zoom, drag nodes, double-click to zoom in, Shift + double-click to zoom out.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Mermaid}: used on Object pages and Validation Rules tabs. Outcome nodes are {\b green} (record saved) or {\b red} (record blocked).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Data Transforms}: explicit data transformation pipeline (input -> mapping -> output).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Analyzer tab}: static analyzer findings with severity (Critical / Major / Minor / Info), description, rationale, remediation and a link to the reference documentation.\sa180\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 6. Configuration menu\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Entry {\b Configuration > Show configuration screen}: opens a window with 3 tabs. Changes are persisted to {\f1 app_settings.json} only when you click {\b Save}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 6.1 Documentation tab\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b General settings}: interface language.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Salesforce}: default environment, instance URL, alias.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Folders and files}: source folder, output folder, exclusion file.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Analysis}: enable PMD + ruleset file.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Reports to generate}: Excel / ORG CHECK checkboxes.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 6.2 Discussion tab\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b AI provider}: {\f1 Gemini} or {\f1 Claude}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Claude key / Gemini key}: masked fields (password-style input).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b System prompt}: multi-line editor with a {\i "Reset to default"} button that restores the prompt shipped with the application (honouring the current language).\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 6.3 Analyzer rules tab\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b File path}: {\f1 src/analyzer/rules.xml} (read-only indicator).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Controls}:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab {\i Enable all / Disable all} (over currently visible rules);\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab {\i Reload from file}: re-reads the XML (drops unsaved edits).\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Filters}: severity, category (Trusted / Easy / Adaptable), scope (apex_class, apex_trigger, flow, object, field, validation_rule, omni_data_transform).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Rule list}: grouped by scope; each row has a checkbox, a colored severity badge, the ID, title and category. An {\i "X/Y active rules"} counter updates in real time.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Details pane}: clicking a rule shows its description, rationale, remediation, source and an {\i "Open reference"} button that opens the underlying documentation (PMD, Well-Architected, Admins, ...).\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 On save, only the {\f1 enabled} attributes are rewritten in {\f1 rules.xml} (comments and whitespace are preserved).\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 7. View scoring (complexity)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Entry {\b Configuration > View scoring}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Enter a weight (non-negative integer) for each component (custom objects, custom fields, record types, validation rules, layouts, custom apps, custom tabs, flows, Apex classes, triggers, OmniStudio).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The live preview reflects the latest generation.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Buttons:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab {\i Reset to default weights};\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab {\i Save}: persists the weights to {\f1 app_settings.json} and injects them into the next documentation build.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The total score and its breakdown are rendered on {\f1 index.html} as a gauge and a per-component table.\sa180\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 8. View Adopt vs Adapt\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Entry {\b Configuration > View Adopt vs Adapt}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Used to assess how heavily the org is customized. "Adopt" (standard) and "Adapt" (custom) components are weighted independently to output a percentage of standard adoption:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Components included: custom objects, custom fields, Apex classes, flows, LWC, FlexiPages, OmniStudio (scripts, IP, cards, data transforms).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The preview updates instantly as you change a weight.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The indicator is displayed on {\f1 index.html} next to the complexity score.\sa180\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 9. Downloads menu\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Direct links to:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Salesforce CLI} ({\f1 sf})\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b PMD} (Apex static analysis)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b ORG CHECK (AppExchange)}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b ORG CHECK (source on GitHub)}\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Each entry opens the matching page in the default browser.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
