{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The execution log (text area at the bottom of the main screen) contains detailed error traces and can be selected / copied.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 11. How to get a Gemini API key and a Claude API key\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The discussion assistant stays neutral: you keep ownership of your key and your account. Keys are stored only in the local {\f1 app_settings.json}. No key is sent anywhere other than the selected provider.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 11.1 Getting a Google Gemini API key\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Gemini offers a generous {\b free tier} (with daily and per-minute quotas). It is the fastest way to try Lucie end-to-end.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Steps}:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Open {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://aistudio.google.com/"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://aistudio.google.com/"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
https://aistudio.google.com/
}}}

}}}
.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Sign in with a {\b Google} account (personal or workspace). Accept the Google AI Studio terms on first visit.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab In the left menu, click {\b "Get API key"}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab Click {\b "Create API key"}:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab either in a brand new Google Cloud project,\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab or by picking an existing project.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 5.\tx360\tab Copy the generated key. It looks like {\f1 AIzaSy...} (alphanumeric, 39 characters).\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Quotas and billing}:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The free tier allows a bounded number of requests per minute and per day. For heavier usage, enable billing on the Google Cloud project that owns the API key and switch to the {\b paid tier}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab See {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/pricing"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/pricing"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/pricing
}}}

}}}
 for up-to-date pricing and the list of models.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Wiring it inside Lucie}:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Open {\b Configuration > Show configuration screen}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Go to the {\b Discussion} tab.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Set {\b AI provider: Gemini}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab Paste the key into the {\b Gemini API key} field.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 5.\tx360\tab Click {\b Save}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 6.\tx360\tab Go back to the main window's {\b Discussion} tab, run at least one documentation generation, and send your first message.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 11.2 Getting an Anthropic Claude API key\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Anthropic does {\b not} offer a free tier: you need a funded account (pay-as-you-go billing, sometimes topped up with trial credits).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Steps}:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Open {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://console.anthropic.com/"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://console.anthropic.com/"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
https://console.anthropic.com/
}}}

}}}
.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Create an account (email + password or Google SSO) or sign in.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Complete the phone verification required on first access.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab In the side bar, go to {\b "Settings"} then {\b "Billing"}:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab load the account with a valid payment method (credit card);\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab a starter credit is often granted to new accounts \u8212- double-check the Billing page to confirm.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 5.\tx360\tab Still under {\b Settings}, go to {\b "API Keys"}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 6.\tx360\tab Click {\b "Create Key"}, give it a descriptive name (for example {\f1 lucie-doc-generator}) and pick the {\b "Default"} scope.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 7.\tx360\tab Copy the generated key. It looks like {\f1 sk-ant-api03-...} (it always starts with {\f1 sk-ant-}).\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li720 \fi0 {\b Important}: Anthropic only reveals the full key once. Copy it into a password manager straight away before closing the dialog.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Models and pricing}:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Lucie uses the {\b Claude 3} model family (the exact model is configured on the service side). Prices are listed at {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.anthropic.com/pricing"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.anthropic.com/pricing"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
https://www.anthropic.com/pricing
}}}

}}}
.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The cost depends on input and output tokens: the org context injected by Lucie typically weighs a few thousand tokens per exchange.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Wiring it inside Lucie}:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Open {\b Configuration > Show configuration screen}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Go to the {\b Discussion} tab.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Set {\b AI provider: Claude}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab Paste the key into the {\b Claude API key} field.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 5.\tx360\tab Click {\b Save}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 6.\tx360\tab From the main window's {\b Discussion} tab, confirm that the provider indicator displays {\i "Claude"} then send your first message.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 11.3 Security best practices\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Never} share an API key in a Git repository, a support ticket or an instant-messaging channel. {\f1 app_settings.json} is excluded from git by default.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Create a distinct key per workstation or per use case and keep its name meaningful in the provider console \u8212- this allows targeted revocation.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab If you suspect a leak, revoke the key immediately (the {\i Delete} button in the provider console) and generate a new one.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Monitor the usage / billing dashboards in each provider's console on a regular basis.\sa180\par}
